modules.description: Schedules output operations for efficient asynchronous writing. Works with `Faraday.bigstring` and `Farjadet.vec` to manage data transmission in network or I/O-bound applications. Useful for streaming large data payloads without excessive memory allocation.

This module directly writes fixed characters, strings, byte sequences, and bigstrings into output buffers. It provides functions for embedding literal values into data streams without dynamic computation. Use it when serializing protocols or file formats with predefined binary segments.

This module offers functions to serialize primitive data types (integers, strings, lists, options) into binary formats with configurable endianness, alongside combinators for composing writers and managing output sequences. It primarily targets encoders like `Faraday`, enabling structured value mapping, subrange handling, and scheduled output operations. Typical use cases include building binary protocols, compact file formats, or streaming data pipelines requiring precise serialization control and compositional flexibility.
